main event: A civilian observer sighted an object that appeared to be Venus in the sky on February 17, 1967.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for one minute,The observer reported the object moving in and out of clouds,The object was described as looking like a bright star,There was no physical evidence or photographs submitted,The conclusion of the report suggested that the observed object was most likely the planet Venus.
sighted object: an object resembling a bright star
witness description: a 14-year-old male who has seen a similar object before
